+  "response": "The time tracking library has been implemented in `src/index.ts` and the associated tests are in `src/index.test.ts`.\n\n### Features Implemented:\n- **Start/Stop Timers**: Implemented `start(taskName)` and `stop()`. Starting a new timer correctly auto-stops the previously running one.\n- **Data Persistence**: Entries are written to a user-provided file path. Directories are automatically created if they do not exist.\n- **Querying & Filtering**: Retrieves all records via `getAllEntries()` and filters by date range through `getEntriesByDateRange(start, end)`.\n- **Summarization**: `summarizeTime()` calculates totals per task (in milliseconds), intelligently utilizing `Date.now()` for actively running tasks.\n- **Error Handling**: Missing task names and stopping a non-existent timer explicitly throw runtime errors.\n- **Unicode Support**: Safely uses `utf8` file serialization to support Emoji and Unicode characters effortlessly.\n\n### Validation:\nI have locally run validation via the workspace configuration:\n- `npm run test` (via Vitest, testing comprehensive behavior, including fake timers for logic validation) - Passed (10/10 tests)\n- `npm run build` (via tsc) - Passed\n- `npm run lint` (via ESLint) - Passed\n\nThe library has zero external dependencies and meets all project constraints.",
